  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\n`geth` returns `chainId=0` for mainnet when not synced. This is an issue because we are displaying the misleading log message\r\n`Invalid eth1 chain id. Please switch to correct chain id` when we should be logging `RemoteNotSynced`.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nWe should log `RemoteNotSynced` or some other log message when we get `chainId=0`\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nJust log RemoteNotSynced if `chainId = 0` (need to check if an unsynced mainnet node is the only case where we can get `chainId=0`).\r\nIf not, we might have to check the sync status and log accordingly.\r\n\r\ncc @paulhauner ",
